Delete a Copy Field Enrichment

Delete a copy field enrichment to stop updating your data from Data Cloud.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To view enrichments in Object Manager:	View Setup
To view a specific enrichment:	You must have access to the data space used in the enrichment.
To create or update a specific enrichment:	

For data space v1: you must have access to the data space used in the enrichment.

For data space v2: for Data Cloud Data Space Management permissions, each data space assigned to you must have the Data Actions feature Customize permissions enabled.


To delete a specific enrichment:	You must have access to the data space used in the enrichment.
To delete enrichments:	Customize Application
OBJECT PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To view enrichments in Object Manager:	Data Action Definition object Read permissions.
To delete enrichments in Object Manager:	Data Action Definition object Create, Update, and Delete permissions.

You must have access as a Data Cloud user to use enrichments.

Deleting a copy field enrichment stops updating the field with data from Data Cloud, but it doesn’t remove the field or data from your org.

From Setup, select Integrations, Enrichments, and then Copy Fields.
Click the name of the enrichment that you want to delete.
Click Delete.
To confirm that you want to delete the enrichment, click Delete again.
